Relicensed emit-only source (authorized)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The certificate emit core and its carrier types were extracted from the
Open Agentic Platform (OAP), where they carry SPDX headers reading
`AGPL-3.0-or-later`. Relicensing this extracted, emit-only source to Apache-2.0
is the prerogative of the sole copyright holder (Bartek Kus) and is an explicit,
authorized act (OAP spec 220-tenant-emit-governance-certificate; the tenant-emit
handoff). The extraction is emit-only by construction: the verifier (the
certificate signature re-check, the stage-artifact re-derivation, the platform-
seal adjudication, and the corpus-binding verify) is excluded and never ported.
That half is vended separately as tenant-tail (spec 219); the verify/emit
boundary is load-bearing (spec 220 AC-6, spec 219 verify-only-by-construction),
so the two tools stay distinct distributables.

Extraction map (OAP source -> tenant-emit destination):

  crates/factory-engine/src/bin/build_certificate.rs
      -> crates/tenant-emit-cli/src/main.rs
         (the `build-certificate` verb, restructured as a subcommand of the
          `tenant-emit` binary; the spec 220 FR-003 --require-operator-key flag
          and the FR-007 corpus read-path are carried verbatim)

  crates/factory-engine/src/governance_certificate.rs
      -> crates/tenant-emit-types/src/certificate.rs   (the cert DTOs)
      -> crates/tenant-emit-core/src/certificate.rs    (the emit engine:
         CertificateBuilder, signing-key resolution, run-dir scan, hash +
         signature, persistence; the verify path is stripped). The lone
         spec-spine seam `validate_spec_id_resolution` is a no-op on the emit
         path (a tenant certificate carries no spec_id) and links no spec-spine
         registry reader.

  crates/factory-engine/src/inter_stage_manifest.rs
      -> crates/tenant-emit-types/src/inter_stage_manifest.rs
         (carrier types only; key-minting / signing / verify stripped -- the
          post-hoc emitter never produces a manifest chain)

  crates/factory-engine/src/pipeline_state.rs
      -> crates/tenant-emit-types/src/pipeline_state.rs
         (trimmed to the minimal slice the post-hoc emitter reads:
          pipeline_id, adapter, build_spec_hash, phase)

The corpus read-path (spec 220 FR-007) reads a spec-spine CorpusAttestation and
hashes it through the public reader seam `spec_spine_core::attest::attestation_hash`.
Read, never recompute (spec 218 FR-002): the attestation-emit / corpus-recompute
surface is banned at the symbol level (clippy.toml disallowed-methods) and the
crate level (cargo-deny ban on `spec-spine-cli`), mirroring OAP's guard.

Per the relicense, OAP's per-file AGPL SPDX header lines are NOT carried into the
ported files; matching spec-spine's convention, the ported files carry no
per-file SPDX header.
